git clone "the repository url" depend if youre connected
git add "filename.extension" = add a specific file to repository 
git commit -m "message" = take a snap shot of actual code 
git status = know number of commit etc etc
git push = push to github with all commits etc etc..
git commit -am "message" = all the changed file not just the one added
git pull = "take the latest version of the file on github"
be aware of merge conflicted by git pull to have the latest version 
resolve conflict and push 
git log = find commit name| who edited | etc...
git reset --hard <commit> = get back to a specific previous version 



git branches for addind new features    
git branch = tell you wich branch youre actually on 
git checkhout -b "name of branch" = create and switch to new branch
git checkhout "nameof branch" = to switch to the branch you want 
git merge "nameof branch" = merge with master branch
